description.narrative: In 2020, the Country Office continued to encourage youth participation in public spaces and to engage young people in a meaningful way by providing them with the tools and opportunities to make their voice heard and to develop their skills and competencies. It promoted the participation of adolescents and young people in advocating for services adapted to their needs, formulating policies, strategies, programming, and improved interactions and dialogue with stakeholders through diverse platforms including U-Report, TV programme Voices of Youth, young reporters, young bloggers, and girls’ empowerment in collaboration with Sephis. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/01/2021
